text: Tittmoning () is a town in Traunstein, in Bavaria, Germany. ==Geography== It is in the historic Rupertiwinkel region, on the left edge of the river Salzach, which forms the border with Ostermiething in the Austrian state of Salzburg. The two communes are linked by a bridge. Tittmoning is about northwest of the Salzburg city centre. ==References== == Sources== *Freed, John B. “Nobles, Ministerials, and Knights in the Archdiocese of Salzburg.” Speculum 62, No. 3 (Jul., 1987): 575–611.
